data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` machinery **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No expression tree construction needed — conditionals work directly inside the lambda body now.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get a numeric suffix appended to disambiguate. This generates a migration renaming columns.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Another renaming migration.

**Fix:** Pin the old names explicitly so no migration is generated:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL for logging)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Add the same parameter to every other method on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
